<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The memset call zeroes the whole pfds buffer on each loop: memset(pfds, 0, MAX_IRQS * sizeof(struct pollfd));. Immediately afterwards the code sets pfds[0] and then populates pfds[1..j-1] for the entries actually used, and then calls poll(pfds, j, -1) where j is the number of initialized entries. Because poll only examines the first j entries and those entries are explicitly initialized, removing the memset would not change program behaviour. Therefore the memset is an executed operation whose removal would not affect behaviour (dead code).
</scenario>

